&nbsp;</font> </p> <p style="LINE-HEIGHT:normal; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:12pt"> <p style="LINE-HEIGHT:normal; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:12pt">&nbsp;</p> <p style="TEXT-ALIGN:center; We also recently began drilling our first well in Tioga County.</font></p> <p style="TEXT-ALIGN:justify; LINE-HEIGHT:normal; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:12pt"> <p style="TEXT-ALIGN:justify; LINE-HEIGHT:normal; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:12pt">&nbsp;</p> <p style="TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:12pt"><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">Two wells have also been drilled near the New York border in Susquehanna County. Early results are positive and work has begun to build a gathering system for future development in this area.</font> </p> <p style="TEXT-ALIGN:justify; LINE-HEIGHT:normal; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:12pt"> <p style="MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:12pt"> <p /> <div style=WIDTH:100%> <p style="TEXT-ALIGN:center; MARGIN:0pt 18pt 0pt 0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:10pt"><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:10pt">- MORE -</font> </p></div> <hr width=100% size=3 style=COLOR:rgb(153,153,153) align=center> <p style=PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:always>&nbsp;</p> <p style="MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:12pt"> <p style="TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:12pt"><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">The graph below provides normalized average daily production data through </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">September</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial"> 30</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">, 2014, for the company&#146;s horizontal wells in the Marcellus Shale. The &#147;pink curve&#148; indicates results for </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">59</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">&nbsp;</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">wells </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">with more than </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">18</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial"> fracture stimulation stages, the &#147;purple curve&#148; indicates results for </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">104</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">&nbsp;</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">wells with 13 to 18 fracture stimulation stages, the &#147;orange curve&#148; indicates results for </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">65</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">&nbsp;</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">wells with 9 to 12 fracture stimulation stages and the &#147;green curve&#148; indicates results for </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">5</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">&nbsp;</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">wells with less than 9 fracture</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial"> stimulation</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial"> stages. The normalized production curves are intended to provide a qualitative indication of the company&#146;s Marcellus Shale wells&#146; performance and should not be used to estimate an individual well&#146;s estimated ultimate recovery. The 4, 8, 12 and 16 Bcf type</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">&nbsp;</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">curves are shown solely for reference purposes and are not intended to be projections of the performance of the company&#146;s wells.</font> </p> <p style="TEXT-ALIGN:justify; In </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">the </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">third</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial"> quarter of 2014, Southwestern placed </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; In the </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">third</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial"> quarter of 2014, the company had </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">23</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">&nbsp;</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">operated wells placed on production which had average times to drill to total depth of </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">5</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial"> days or less from re-entry to re-entry. FONT-SIZE:12pt"><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">In the Upper Fayetteville formation, the company has placed 15 wells on production</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial"> to date</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; The first horizontal well is currently drilling</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial"> and </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">an</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial"> additional vertical well</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">&nbsp;</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">is planned for</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial"> the </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">fourth quarter</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">.&nbsp; </font></p> <p style="TEXT-ALIGN:justify; LINE-HEIGHT:normal; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:12pt"> <p style="TEXT-ALIGN:justify; LINE-HEIGHT:normal; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:12pt">&nbsp;</p> <p style="TEXT-ALIGN:justify; LINE-HEIGHT:100%; TEXT-INDENT:0pt; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:CG Times; FONT-SIZE:12pt"><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; TEXT-DECORATION:underline">Explanation and Reconciliation of Non-GAAP Financial Measures</font> </p> <p style="BORDER-BOTTOM:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt; TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE:12pt"> <p style="BORDER-BOTTOM:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt; TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE:12pt">&nbsp;</p> <p style="BORDER-BOTTOM:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt; TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE:12pt; BORDER-TOP:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt"><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">The company reports its financial results in accordance with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America (&#147;GAAP&#148;). However, management believes certain non-GAAP performance measures may provide </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">financial statement </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">users </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">with </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">additional meaningful comparisons between current results and the results of its peers and of prior periods.&nbsp; </font></p> <p style="BORDER-BOTTOM:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt; TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE:12pt; BORDER-TOP:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt"> <p style="BORDER-BOTTOM:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt; TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE:12pt; BORDER-TOP:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt">&nbsp;</p> <p style="BORDER-BOTTOM:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt; TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE:12pt; BORDER-TOP:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt"><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">One such non-GAAP financial measure is net cash provided by operating activities before changes in operating assets and liabilities. Management presents this measure because (i) it is accepted as an indicator of an oil and gas exploration and production company&#146;s ability to internally fund exploration and development activities and to service or incur additional debt, (ii) changes in operating assets and liabilities relate to the timing of cash receipts and disbursements which the company may not control and (iii) changes in operating assets and liabilities may not relate to the period in which the operating activities occurred.</font> </p> <p style="BORDER-BOTTOM:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt; TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE:12pt; BORDER-TOP:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt"> <p style="BORDER-BOTTOM:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt; TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE:12pt; BORDER-TOP:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt">&nbsp;</p> <p style="BORDER-BOTTOM:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt; TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE:12pt; BORDER-TOP:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt"><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">Additional non-GAAP financial measures the company may present from time to time are </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">adjusted </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">net income, </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">adjusted </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">diluted earnings per share</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">, adjusted EBITDA</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt"> and its E&amp;P segment operating income, all which exclude certain charges or amounts. Management presents these measures because (i) they are consistent with the manner in which the company&#146;s performance is measured relative to the performance of its peers, (ii) these measures are more comparable to earnings estimates provided by securities analysts, and (iii) charges or amounts excluded cannot be reasonably estimated and guidance provided by the company excludes information regarding these types of items. These adjusted amounts are not a measure of financial performance under GAAP. </font></p> <p style="TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE:12pt; BORDER-TOP:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt"> <p style="MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:12pt"> <p /> <div style=WIDTH:100%> <p style="TEXT-ALIGN:center; MARGIN:0pt 18pt 0pt 0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:10pt"><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:10pt">- MORE -</font> </p></div> <hr width=100% size=3 style=COLOR:rgb(153,153,153) align=center> <p style=PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:always>&nbsp;</p> <p style="MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:12pt"> <p style="BORDER-BOTTOM:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt; TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE:12pt"><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">See the reconciliations below of GAAP financial measures to non-GAAP financial measures for the three </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">and </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">nine</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">&nbsp;</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">months ended </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">Septemb</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">er</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt"> and </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">September</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt"> 30</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">, 201</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">3</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">, respectively</font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial; FONT-SIZE:12pt">. Non-GAAP financial measures should not be considered in isolation or as a substitute for the company's reported results prepared in accordance with GAAP.</font> </p> <p style="BORDER-BOTTOM:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt; TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE:12pt">&nbsp;</p> <p style="TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE:12pt; BORDER-TOP:rgb(217,217,217) 1pt" /> <div style=WIDTH:100%> <table bordercolor=transparent style="WIDTH:486pt; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:12pt">&nbsp;</p> <p style="TEXT-ALIGN:justify; MARGIN:0pt; FONT-FAMILY:Courier; FONT-SIZE:12pt"><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">All statements, other than historical facts and financial information, may be deemed to be forward-looking statements within the meaning of Section 27A of the Securities Act of 1933, as amended, and Section 21E of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended. the company&#146;s ability to transport its production to the most favorable markets or at all; the timing and extent of the company&#146;s success in discovering, developing, producing and estimating reserves; the economic viability of, and the company&#146;s success in drilling, the company&#146;s large acreage position in the Fayetteville Shale, overall as well as relative to other productive shale gas areas; the company&#146;s ability to fund the company&#146;s planned capital investments; the impact of federal, state and local government regulation, including any legislation relating to hydraulic fracturing, the climate or over the counter derivatives; the company&#146;s ability to determine the most effective and economic fracture stimulation for the Fayetteville Shale and the Marcellus Shale; the costs and availability of oil field personnel services and drilling supplies, raw materials, and equipment and services; the company&#146;s future property acquisition or divestiture activities; increased competition; the </font><font style="DISPLAY:inline; FONT-FAMILY:Arial">financial impact of accounting regulations and critical accounting policies;
